      <ResourceHeader>
         <ResourceName>Observation data taken by the visible all-sky camera at Shigaraki MU Observatory</ResourceName>
         <ReleaseDate>2016-07-21T18:24:00</ReleaseDate>
         <Description>The observation data taken by the visible all-sky camera at Shigaraki MU Observatory in Shiga Prefecture, Japan (34.86N, 136.11E, 385m MSL), which has been operated on November 4, 2010. File names of observation data are composed of date and time: (year)(month)(day)_(hour)(minute).jpg. The time interval of each image is 1 minutes. Local time (UT + 09:00) is used for time data.</Description>
         <Acknowledgement>If you acquire Shigaraki All Sky Camera data, we ask that you acknowledge us in your use of the data. This may be done by including text such as All Sky Camera data at Shigaraki were provided by Research Institute for Sustainable Humanosphere of Kyoto University. We would also appreciate receiving a copy of the relevant publications.</Acknowledgement>
